The Litany was followed by a prayer said by the bishop. This was the Collectio post precem. It sums up the petitione already recited. The following is the form for use on the Nativity from the Missa-ale Gothicum :—

Exaudi, Domine, familiam tibi dicatam et in tuae ecclesiae gremio in hac hodierna solemnitate Nativitatis tuae congregatam ut laudes tuas exponat. Tribue captivis redemptionem, caecis visum, peccantibus remissionem3 quia tu venisti ut salvos facias nos. Aspice de caelo sancto tuo et inlumina populum tuum, quorum animus in te plena devotione confidit, Salvator mundi, qui vivis, etc.

This collect corresponds With the prayer Κύριε παντο- κράτορ, in the Liturgy of the Apostolical Oonsffitntions,
